# scripts/forbidden-terms.local.example
#
# Copy this file to scripts/forbidden-terms.local (which is gitignored) and
# add the internal references that must never be committed to the public
# repository. The pre-commit secret scanner (scripts/check-secrets.sh) reads
# the .local file and blocks any commit whose staged content matches.
#
# Format: one extended-regex (grep -E) pattern per line.
# Blank lines and lines beginning with '#' are ignored.
#
# Examples (replace with your own — keep this example file generic):
#   "Some Internal Program Name"
#   internal-codename
#   private-partner\.example\.com
